  "text": "The study of photoexcited charge carriers in nanoparticles, although very demanding, must be performed by using a hybrid functional method (here B3LYP), since any other local or semilocal functional, and therefore also DFTB, would not properly describe the degree of electron/hole localization as a consequence of the self-interaction problem inherent in those methods [CITATION_1] . DFT+U approach could be an alternative viable route; however, hole trapping was found to required very high and unphysical U values [CITATION_2] .",
